title: Kucharowo
text:
Kucharowo (German: "Kucherow") is a <a href="village">village</a> in the administrative district of <a href="Gmina%20Borne%20Sulinowo">Gmina Borne Sulinowo</a>, within <a href="Szczecinek%20County">Szczecinek County</a>, <a href="West%20Pomeranian%20Voivodeship">West Pomeranian Voivodeship</a>, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately north of <a href="Borne%20Sulinowo">Borne Sulinowo</a>, south-west of <a href="Szczecinek">Szczecinek</a>, and east of the regional capital <a href="Szczecin">Szczecin</a>.
Before 1945 the area was part of <a href="Germany">Germany</a>. For the history of the region, see <a href="History%20of%20Pomerania">History of Pomerania</a>.
